divs: Sighting DetailsOn January 29th about 6 P.M. I was taking pictures of the Queen Mary. Later that evening I downloaded my pictures off my digital camera and then I realized there were 4 oval lights in one of my photos. My camera was on a long exposure and has exagerated the lights a little but yet these lights do not seem to be a reflection of any other lights in the area. My friends have reviewed the photo but no one seems to have an explanation. * I am submitting my photo to you. Would you please inform me of your thoughts? * If you need a better quality i can send it too. This is half the quality jpg puts out.
Summary: 4 oval lights in the sky above the Queen Mary in the LA Harbor.
